    },
    {
      "is_private": false,
      "reactions": {},
      "id": 17852461,
      "text": "Created attachment 9538985\nBug 2011616 - Remove AndroidHardwareBufferApi wrapper. r?#gfx-reviewers\n\n\nOur minimum SDK version is now high enough that all the currently\nrequired functions are available. And if we want to use more recently\nadded functions in the future we now support weak NDK symbols. So the\nAPI wrapper is unnecessary.\n\nOne thing to note is that we currently use the return value of\nAndroidHardwareBufferApi::Get() (i.e. whether the API wrapper was\ninitialised) to determine whether our compositors need to create a\nrelease fence at the end of the frame. This is changed to check\nwhether AndroidHardwareBufferManager is initialised instead.",
      "bug_id": 2011616,
      "creation_time": "2026-01-21T09:27:30Z",
      "creator": "jnicol@mozilla.com",
      "raw_text": "\nOur minimum SDK version is now high enough that all the currently\nrequired functions are available. And if we want to use more recently\nadded functions in the future we now support weak NDK symbols. So the\nAPI wrapper is unnecessary.\n\nOne thing to note is that we currently use the return value of\nAndroidHardwareBufferApi::Get() (i.e. whether the API wrapper was\ninitialised) to determine whether our compositors need to create a\nrelease fence at the end of the frame. This is changed to check\nwhether AndroidHardwareBufferManager is initialised instead.",
      "time": "2026-01-21T09:27:30Z",
      "count": 1,
      "tags": [],
      "author": "jnicol@mozilla.com",
      "attachment_id": 9538985
    },
